column11:
  The rare pion decays ${\pi}^+{ightarrow}{\mu}^+{
u}_{\mu}{
u} ar{
u}$
and ${\pi}^+{ightarrow}e^+{
u}_{e}{
u} ar{
u}$ are allowed in the
Standard Model but highly suppressed. These decays were searched for using data
from the PIENU experiment. A first result for
${\Gamma}({\pi}^+{ightarrow}{\mu}^+{
u}_{\mu}{
u} ar{
u})/{\Gamma}({\pi}^+{ightarrow}{\mu}^+{
u}_{\mu})<8.6{	imes}10^{-6}$,
and an improved measurement
${\Gamma}({\pi}^+{ightarrow}{e}^+{
u}_{e}{
u} ar{
u})/{\Gamma}({\pi}^+{ightarrow}{\mu}^+{
u}_{\mu})<1.6{	imes}10^{-7}$
were obtained.
